{
  "stem": "21626.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Thomas-- Tomas' and Janus' parents died, we think, in Lodz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think, you know, they were gassed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because the professional families from Prague, most of them went-- went to Lodz straight without going to Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [SIGHS] I still got Auntie Marta's engagement ring.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this is my mother's.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Anyway, my mother-- my auntie-- as I said, Auntie Berta, lived with her parents.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they had a beautiful flat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But after they'd been taken to the camps, the flat was given to the local butcher, who had a young family.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And no way could she get the flat back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were loading it with-- with her father's furniture, you know, and everything.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she had to make do in sharing a two room flat which belonged to a cousin of my mother's and his wife.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Their name was Karel and her name was Milla, who were quite a bit younger.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, it was the younger ones who survived more easily, because they were useful as work-- workhorses, and stronger.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so I moved in there as well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't mind the cramped conditions.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And luckily, they didn't.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We all needed each other.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We helped each other, though nobody could talk about the past at that time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Nobody could.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But I did learn that Karel, who's the same namesake of my father, was together with my father in the camps almost to the end.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And Milla was together with Aunt Berta and my mother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So that created a tremendous bond, of course, between us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there were lots of heartwarming things said, which we did talk about-- my mother's courtship with my father when Karel, who was a young lad then-- was their go between, and you know, one who brought love letters from one to the other.",
      "word_count": 44
    }
  ],
